{
  "id": "11",
  "name": "Imputing With Constant",
  "description": "It imputes missing value with constant value. It fills missing values (None) in selected columns with given constant value for the corresponding column, in the incoming DataFrame.",
  "type": "transform",
  "engine":"all",
  "nodeClass": "fire.nodes.ml.NodeReplaceMissingValueWithConstant",
  "fields" : [
    {"name": "colNames", "value":"[]", "widget": "variables_list_select", "title": "Columns", "description": "Columns to be processed for missing values"},

    {"name": "constants", "value":"[]", "widget": "variables_list_textfield", "title": "Constants", "description": "Missing value will be replaced with constant"}


  ]
}

start-details:

This node imputes the missing value with constant value.

It fills missing values (None) in selected columns with given constant value for the corresponding column, in the incoming DataFrame.

end-details:

start-examples:

Incoming Dataframe has following rows and [AGE] column has missing values / [NULL] for some rows:

CUST_CD    |    CUST_NAME    |    AGE
-----------------------------------------
CD01       |    DAVID        |    30
CD02       |    MARY         |    40
CD03       |    PAUL         |			
CD04       |    MATT         |			

If imputingwithconstatnt node is configured to Impute [AGE] with 45 then missing values in [AGE] column would be replaced with 45.
Outgoing Dataframe would result as below:

CUST_CD    |    CUST_NAME    |    AGE
-----------------------------------------
CD01       |    DAVID        |    30
CD02       |    MARY         |    40
CD03       |    PAUL         |    45			
CD04       |    MATT         |    45			

end-examples:
